, but just apparent truth=\r\ns and not absolute truths.\n=C2=A0\nIf a character in a movie is wearing red =\r\nshirt and everybody sees red shirt, wearing red shirt is a truth. Someone m=\r\nay say it is just a delusion and there is no real person there, i.e. it is =\r\njust a movie. While it is a bigger truth that it is but a movie and not rea=\r\nlly happening, it is also true that someone is wearing a red shirt in the m=\r\novie. Similarly, if a mirror is reflecting Sun, Sun in the mirror is said t=\r\no be a delusion. But one can say that Sun in mirror is an apparent reality =\r\nand the real Sun outside of the mirror is the absolute reality. When the mi=\r\nrror is withdrawn, apparent reality disappears.\n=C2=A0\nSatya Narayana stand=\r\ns for the absolute Truth as well as how it manifests as various apparent Tr=\r\nuths. That is why he is accompanied by several other deities (see below).\n=\r\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\n=C2=A0=C2=A0 Ganesha (one who removes obstac=\r\nles):\nOM gaM gaNapataye namaH svaahaa, gaNapataya idaM na mama\n=C2=A0\n=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 Varuna (one who gives persistence to fight obstacles):\nOM vaM var=\r\nuNaaya namaH svaahaa, varuNaayedaM na mama \n=C2=A0\n=C2=A0=C2=A0 Pancha loka=\r\n palakas (rulers of five elements):\nOM gaNapataye namaH svaahaa, gaNapataya=\r\n idaM na mama (earth - solid form state)\nOM brahmaNe namaH svaahaa, brahmaN=\r\na idaM na mama (air - expansive state)\nOM mahaalakSmyai namaH svaahaa, maha=\r\nalakShmyaa idaM na mama (ether - basic space state)\nOM mahaaviShNave namaH =\r\nsvaahaa, mahaaviShNava idaM na mama (same as above)\nOM rudraaya namaH svaah=\r\naa, rudraayedaM na mama (fire - transformatory state)\nOM gauryai namaH svaa=\r\nhaa, gauryaa idaM na mama (water - liquid/flexible form state)\n=C2=A0\n=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 Navagrahas along with ruling and co-ruling deities (aspects of co=\r\nnsciousness):\nOM sUryaaya namaH svaahaa, sUryaayedaM na mama (Sun =3D soul)=\r\n\nOM agnaye namaH svaahaa, agnaya idaM na mama\nOM rudraaya namaH svaahaa, ru=\r\ndraayedaM na mama\nOM chandraaya namaH svaahaa, chandraayedaM na mama (Moon =\r\n=3D mind)\nOM apbhyo namaH svaahaa, apbhya idaM na mama\nOM gauryai namaH sva=\r\nahaa, gauryaa idaM na mama\nOM kujaaya namaH svaahaa, kujaayedaM na mama (Ma=\r\nrs =3D energy and initiative)\nOM pR^ithivyai namaH svaahaa, pR^ithivyaa ida=\r\nM na mama\nOM kShetrapaalakaaya namaH svaahaa, kShetrapaalakaayedaM na mama\n=\r\nOM budhaaya namaH svaahaa, budhaayedaM na mama (Mercury =3D flexibility and=\r\n learning ability)\nOM viShnave namaH svaahaa, viShnava idaM na mama\nOM naar=\r\naayaNaaya namaH svaahaa, naaraayaNaayedaM na mama\nOM bR^ihaspataye namaH sv=\r\naahaa, bR^ihaspataya idaM na mama (Jupiter =3D wisdom, discretion and judgm=\r\nent)\nOM brahmaNe namaH svaahaa, brahmaNa idaM na mama\nOM indraaya namaH sva=\r\nahaa, indraayiedaM na mama\nOM shukraaya namaH svaahaa, shukraayedaM na mama=\r\n (Venus =3D spirit of happiness)\nOM indraaNyai namaH svaahaa, indraaNyaa id=\r\naM na mama\nOM indramarutvantaaya namaH svaahaa, indramarutvantaayedaM na ma=\r\nma\nOM shanaishcharaaya namaH svaahaa, shanaishcharaayedaM na mama (Saturn =\r\n=3D spirit of work, persistence and discipline)\nOM yamaaya namaH svaahaa, y=\r\namaayedaM na mama\nOM prajaapateye namaH svaahaa, prajaapateya idaM na mama\n=\r\nOM raahave namaH svaahaa, raahava idaM na mama (Rahu =3D spirit of breaking=\r\n barriers)\nOM gomaatre namaH svaahaa, gomaatra idaM na mama\nOM sarpebhyo na=\r\nmaH svaahaa, sarpebhya idaM na mama\nOM ketave namaH svaahaa, ketava idaM na=\r\n mama (Ketu =3D detachment)\nOM chitraguptaaya namaH svaahaa, chitraguptaaye=\r\ndaM na mama\nOM brahmaNe namaH svaahaa, brahmaNa idaM na mama\n=C2=A0\n=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0 Dasa Dikpalakas (rulers of ten direction we take in life, in terms o=\r\nf our work):\nOM indraaya namaH svaahaa, indraayedaM na mama (Indra =3D Powe=\r\nr and influence over others)\nOM agnaye namaH svaahaa, agnaya idaM na mama (=\r\nAgni =3D Transformation of world)\nOM yamaaya namaH svaahaa, yamaayedaM na m=\r\nama (Yama =3D Enforcement of rules and righteousness)\nOM nirR^itaye namaH s=\r\nvaahaa, nirR^itaya idaM na mama (Nirriti =3D Cutting edge work and breaking=\r\n barriers/rules)\nOM varuNaaya namaH svaahaa, varuNaayedaM na mama (Varuna =\r\n=3D Making relations with others and interacting with others)\nOM vaayave na=\r\nmaH svaahaa, vaayava idaM na mama (Vayu =3D Strengthening people)\nOM somaay=\r\na namaH svaahaa, somaayedaM na mama (Soma/Kubera =3D Nourishing and enrichi=\r\nng people)\nOM Ishaanaaya namaH svaahaa, IshaanaayedaM na mama (Ishana =3D T=\r\neaching and informing people of good things)\nOM brahmaNe namaH svaahaa, bra=\r\nhmaNa idaM na mama (Brahma =3D Research and investigation)\nOM ananta sheSha=\r\naya namaH svaahaa, ananta sheShaayedaM na mama (Ananta Sesha =3D Supporting=\r\n various structures)\n=C2=A0\n=C2=A0=C2=A0 Satya Narayana (Truth personified)=\r\n:\nOM namo bhagavate satyadevaaya svaahaa, satyadevaayedaM na mama\n=C2=A0\nDo=\r\n the last one as many times as you want. When done, switch to the main homa=\r\nm and proceed with uttaraangam. You can also meditate with the 12-lettered =\r\nmantra &quot;OM namo bhagavate satyadevaaya&quot; at the end of homam.\n=C2=A0\nThis is=\r\n equivalent to doing a Satya Narayana vratam and powerful on a Full Moon da=\r\ny (e.g. today), Ekadashi day or Ravi Sankramana (solar ingress into siderea=\r\nl signs) day. Particularly, Full Moon days of vaishaakha, kaartIka and maag=\r\nha months are particular auspicious for this as per Lord Vishnu&#39;s words to =\r\nSage Narada.\n=C2=A0\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n-------------------------------=\r\n------------------------------------\n=C2=A0 Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyo=\r\ntish Lessons, Jyotish Writings,\n&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short H=\r\nomam and Pitri Tarpana:\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A