n us as our discipline, patience and persistence. Yama lives=\r\n within us as discipline and the ability to follow rules. Nirriti lives wit=\r\nhin us as the spirit of discovery and crossing barriers. And so on. If thos=\r\ne qualities are firmly established in one&#39;s consciousness, what seat is off=\r\nered to corresponding deities in the ritual is highly secondary! \n=C2=A0 \nI=\r\nrrespective of what seat you use (made of grains arranged in a shape or bet=\r\nel lead or just rice grains), contemplate the nature represented by the dei=\r\nty and imagine that the deity has really come and sat there. \n=C2=A0 \nBest =\r\nregards, \nNarasimha \n------------------------------------------------------=\r\n------------- \n=C2=A0 Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish =\r\nWritings, \n&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and Pitri Tarpan=\r\na: \n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 http://www.VedicAstrologer.org \n=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 Films that make a difference: http://SaraswatiFilms.org \n=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 Spirituality: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-=\r\nwisdom \n=C2=A0 Jyotish writings: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWriti=\r\nngs \n------------------------------------------------------------------- \n=\r\n=C2=A0 \n\nOn Wed, Feb 16, 2011 at 10:29 PM, nagraj@... wrote: \n\n=\r\n=C2=A0 =C2=A0 Namaste, \n\nIs there anything to substitute the beetel leaves =\r\nin Satya Narayana Vratam? In the US, sometimes they are not available unles=\r\ns arrangements are made well in advance. Tomorrow is Pournimasya and we int=\r\nended to do the Satyanarayana Vratam and we are having difficulty in procur=\r\ning the beetel leaves. \n\nNagraj \n\n\n\n\n\n\r\n--0-761719339-1298064667=:33868\r\nContent-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable\r\n\r\n&lt;table cellspacing=3D&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=3D&quot;0&