;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n=\r\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;Some people=\r\n call lower truths as delusions. But it is a matter of nomenclature. Those =\r\nare also truths, but just apparent truths and not absolute truths.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/=\r\nDIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;=\r\n&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerda=\r\nna&gt;If a character in a movie is wearing red shirt and everybody sees red sh=\r\nirt, wearing red shirt is a truth. Someone may say it is just a delusion an=\r\nd there is no real person there, i.e. it is just a movie. While it is a big=\r\nger truth that it is but a movie and not really happening, it is also true =\r\nthat someone is wearing a red shirt in the movie. Similarly, if a mirror is=\r\n reflecting Sun, Sun in the mirror is said to be a delusion. But one can sa=\r\ny that Sun in mirror is an apparent reality and the real Sun outside of the=\r\n mirror is the absolute reality. When the mirror is withdrawn, apparent rea=\r\nlity disappears.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=\r\n=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#00=\r\n0000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;Satya Narayana stands for the absolute Truth a=\r\ns well as how it manifests as various apparent Truths. That is why he is ac=\r\ncompanied by several other deities (see below).&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dl=\r\neft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV =\r\nalign=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/=\r\nFONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana=\r\n&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&