DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp; &lt;=\r\n/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdan=\r\na&gt;If you just lay out a few rice grains for each deity and place the idol/c=\r\noin on them, that is fine too. &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=\r\n=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;=\r\nFONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;The planets and deities are al=\r\nready within us. For example, Jupiter lives in us as our wisdom and judgmen=\r\nt. Saturn lives within us as our discipline, patience and persistence. Yama=\r\n lives within us as discipline and the ability to follow rules. Nirriti liv=\r\nes within us as the spirit of discovery and crossing barriers. And so on. I=\r\nf those qualities are firmly established in one&#39;s consciousness, what seat =\r\nis offered to corresponding deities in the ritual is highly secondary! &lt;/FO=\r\nNT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&=\r\nnbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=\r\n=3DVerdana&gt;Irrespective of what seat you use (made of grains arranged in a =\r\nshape or betel lead or just rice grains), contemplate the nature represente=\r\nd by the deity and imagine that the deity has really come and sat there. &lt;/=\r\nFONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana=\r\n&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=\r\n=3DVerdana&gt;Best regards, &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000=\r\n000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;Narasimha &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT=\r\n color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;----------------------------------=\r\n---------